{
  "page": "Hobb the Hewer",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Hobb the Hewer</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Hobbthehewer.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Hobbthehewer.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/bc/Hobbthehewer.png/300px-Hobbthehewer.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/bc/Hobbthehewer.png/450px-Hobbthehewer.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/bc/Hobbthehewer.png/600px-Hobbthehewer.png 2x\" /></a><div>Hobb the Hewer by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://ashleyhunterrice.tumblr.com/\">Ashley Hunter Rice</a></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Hobb the Hewer</b> was a woodsman who gained fame during the civil war known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hobb_the_Hewer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Storming_of_the_Dragonpit\" title=\"Storming of the Dragonpit\">Storming of the Dragonpit</a>, Hobb managed to slay <a href=\"/index.php/Shrykos\" title=\"Shrykos\">Shrykos</a> when he leapt on the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>'s neck, driving his axe into the beast's skull as Shrykos tried to shake him off. Hobb locked his legs around the dragon's neck and continued to rain blows on its skull, calling out the names of the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Seven</a>. The seventh blow (known as <a href=\"/index.php/Stranger_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Stranger (the Seven)\">the Stranger</a>'s blow) ended Shrykos's life.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a> wrote that Hobb slew the dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Syrax\" title=\"Syrax\">Syrax</a> as well, but most historians concur this is highly unlikely. It is unknown if Hobb survived the collapsing of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hobb_the_Hewer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Hobb the Hewer and <a href=\"/index.php/Three-Finger_Hobb\" title=\"Three-Finger Hobb\">Three-Finger Hobb</a> may have been named by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> after author <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robin_Hobb\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Robin Hobb\">Robin Hobb</a>, whose writing Martin has admired.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hobb_the_Hewer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Overthrown.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/946\">Authors Worthy of Legends</a>, November 11, 1998</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_A_Blog\" title=\"Not A Blog\">Not A Blog</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://georgerrmartin.com/notablog/2021/07/30/lords-of-fantasy/\">Lords of Fantasy</a>, July 30, 2021</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404073604\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.065 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.244 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 661/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10532/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5047/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1338/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2247/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.160/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.44 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  234.695      1 -total\n 95.63%  224.441      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 95.09%  223.176      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.78%   27.640     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  2.99%    7.021      3 Template:Ref\n  2.32%    5.434      2 Template:Infobox_label\n  1.85%    4.348      3 Template:Ref/core\n  1.00%    2.344   